> Our Spring Panzanella Salad is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat
> more veg in your diet and try something new!

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Pop the potatoes and onion onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, add the @dried oregano{1%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks and pop onto a #baking tray{} in a single layer.

Drizzle with @olive oil{1} for the garlic bread, season with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{} and the garlic, then toss to coat well.

Bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and set aside.

Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre. Leave to one side for now.

When the veg has ~{8-10%minutes} of roasting time left, add the @sugar snap peas{80%g} to the baking tray.

Toss with the onion and potatoes, then return the veg to the oven for the remaining time until cooked.

Meanwhile, add the @fresh pesto{50%g} to a small #bowl{}. Pour in the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} for the dressing and @honey{1%tbsp}, then squeeze in the @lemon{1}(juiced) juice. Stir until combined.

Taste the dressing and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When ready, stir together the roast veg, croutons and pesto dressing in a large bowl (or just on a baking tray).

Let everything sit for a couple of mins (the ciabatta will absorb the flavours), then stir through the courgette ribbons and @baby leaf mix{50%g}. Season with salt and pepper.

Share the panzanella salad between your plates and crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} over the top to finish.

Enjoy!